cs.IT, cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the concept of power-domain NOMA and its application in hybrid uplink NOMA. This falls under the purview of information theory.
2. cs.GT (Game Theory) - The paper uses evolutionary game theory to analyze the behavior of users in hybrid uplink NOMA. This makes it highly likely to belong to the game theory sub-category.
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the design and analysis of a communication system, which is a key aspect of networking and internet architecture.
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper uses evolutionary game theory to model the behavior of users in a communication system. This can be seen as a social network where users interact with each other.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - Although not directly related to multimedia, the paper deals with the concept of power control, which is a key aspect of multimedia communication systems.
